snippet.textDisplay:
Nothing to do with the video, but I need to jot this down before I forget. I had a weird dream this morning (I just woke up) and... It was just a random dream. Stuff about my fear of stairs, finding arcades that inspire d console computer games, whatever.
But then, at the end, I dreamed you guys were doing a second (third?) TMPH where you put on costumes, except they were bad, and you got professionals to do your makeup. Tucker got a costume first, then Arin, then Dan. Also the makeup. I can't remember anyone's costume but Arin's, because it was a hotdog with mustard that lit up when you pressed a button on a remote.
Dan had all his stuff put on him, and Tucker and Arin were sitting in the back for some reason (space for the cosmotolomakeuppros?)??? And when Dan's look was finished, he was talking about how "hawt" he looked, in the "I just wanna get fucked/That bitch Stacy" voice. Somehow, this led to them beatboxing (acapella-ing???) this song, which may or may not exist:

1, 6, 5, 4, 5, 2,2. 1, 6, 5, 4, 5, 8,8
repeat twice, then add a beat that's 2 hits a second. It escalates further, but I woke up.
(1 is the lowest note, 8 is the highest, and I tried to use format to indicate spaces and timing, but that's hard to get through in text [I wish you could make music sheets in text, with emojis or something, something universal] also I'm not even sure I got the notes highness and lowness correct. I just woke and I know nothing of music. It's hard to figure out the notes of a fast paced song, sorry)
Eventually the whole crew gets involved with the song, and Tucker starts using the remote to the hotdog suit to make it light up in sync with everyone. Arin starts going, "Ow, stop it. Ow, it hurts OW. OW! AAAAAAAAAAA!" LIKE he does, and everything halts while he takes off the hotdog. Danny turns to look at him and says, "Were you getting shocked?" and Arin, back to his normal volume, goes, "it was just a bit" And Dan breaks out into his signature laughter, and then I woke up.

Seriously, though, if anyone can understand how I wrote the beat of the song, can you help me find it? I'm quite certain I've heard it somewhere before.
